{"title":"DMT GK1 Gravel Shoes Feature a Michelin Rubber Sole","link":"https://theradavist.com/dmt-gk1-gravel-shoes-feature-a-michelin-rubber-sole/","date":1711549285000,"content":"<p><img width=\"3000\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?fit=1200,2000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_Shoes.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>One thing we’ve noted over the past few years are the number of smaller footwear brands popping up. DMT is one of those brands and its <a href=\"https://dmtcycling.com/en-us/products/dmt-gk1-shoes-gravel-black-bordeaux-m0010dmt22gk1-a\" target=\"_blank\">GK1 Gravel shoe</a> ($230) just came across our radar.<span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"3000\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?fit=1200,2000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/DMT_Gravel_colors.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The GK1 features a full knit upper construction for a very light cycling shoe with great breathability. It has just enough stretch to perfectly match your foot shape, while the integrated, reflective, and reinforced laces guarantee mud and abrasion protection.</p>\n<p>It features a Michelin® outsole that has a specific compound tread design, with a unique geometry and lug shape, all custom designed to provide outstanding traction and grip when you need foot control on the ground or when getting off the bike.</p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://dmtcycling.com/en-us/products/dmt-gk1-shoes-gravel-black-ocra-m0010dmt22gk1-a#accordion_container\" target=\"_blank\">DMT</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/dmt-gk1-gravel-shoes-feature-a-michelin-rubber-sole/\">DMT GK1 Gravel Shoes Feature a Michelin Rubber Sole</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"437777d44576225fb72687755aecb9583f3271d273ed2725a7c381f4f5853224","category":"Cycling"}